Dataset of IoT-Based Energy and Environmental Parameters in a Smart Building Infrastructure
==========================================================================================

Source: IoT sensors deployed in the M5 building of the institution.
Date range: January – June 2024

This dataset is a merged long-format CSV derived from 48 original CSV files covering:

ENERGY CONSUMPTION (7 appliances):
  Coffee Machine, Desktop, Fridge, Kettle, Microwave, Printer, Water Dispenser
  Metrics: Watt (W), Current (A), Voltage (V), Apparent Power (VA), Energy (kWh/today, kWh/total)

ENVIRONMENTAL (3 locations):
  Lab (Interdisciplinary), Kitchen, Mailroom
  Metrics: Temperature (°C), Humidity (%)

OCCUPANCY (3 locations):
  Lab (motion + door), Kitchen, Mailroom
  Metrics: Motion state

CSV COLUMNS:
  time               - ISO 8601 timestamp with timezone offset (+04:00)
  category           - Sensor category (e.g., watt_w, temperature, humidity, motion)
  device_or_location - Appliance name or room (e.g., coffee_machine, lab, mailroom)
  value              - Numeric sensor reading
  unit               - Unit of measurement (W, A, V, VA, kWh, °C, %, state)

MQTT TOPIC STRUCTURE:
  building/m5/<category>/<device_or_location>
  Example: building/m5/watt_w/coffee_machine

Generated by: devices/smart_building_m5/create_dataset.py
